<h3>FAQ Document Help</h3>

<p>
The FAQ document administration allows you to define the documents,
each of which contains a set of questions.  Define as many documents
as you need by adding them one-by-one.
</p>

<p>
You may edit the FAQ document at any time, even after questions have
been added to the document.  Making changes to the document will not have
any effect on the questions.  Of course any changes to the Introduction
or Epilogue will change the content of the entire document.
</p>

<p>
Be careful about deleting documents.  When you do this, any questions
that are associated with a FAQ document will be deleted as well.  The
deletion of a document (and it's questions) is permanent and cannot be
undone.
</p>

